text: Robert George "Bobby" Seale (born October 22, 1936) is an American political activist. He was born in Dallas, Texas. He and fellow activist Huey P. Newton co-founded the Black Panther Party. He was briefly a member of the Chicago Eight. ==References== ==Other websites== * Interview in Detroit, 1978, American Black Journal Category:1936 births Category:Living people Category:American political activists Category:People from Dallas
